-- 1NF:
-- All columns contain atomic (single) values.
-- No column stores multiple values in one field.
-- Example: email and first_name each contain only one value.

-- 2NF:
-- All non-key attributes are fully dependent on the primary key.
-- In the enrollments table, grade and enrollment_date depend on the complete enrollment record.
-- There are no partial dependencies.

-- 3NF:
-- There are no transitive dependencies.
-- Department information is stored only in the departments table.
-- Students store only department_id, avoiding redundancy.
